Pre-baked MLPs and ground-truth statistics for the WhestBench competition.

## Quick start

```python
from datasets import load_dataset

ds = load_dataset(
    "{{ repo_id }}",
    revision="{{ revision }}",
    split="{{ split }}",
)
print(ds)
print(ds[0]["mlp_name"])
```

Or via the whestbench convenience wrapper (adds schema validation + metadata):

```python
import whestbench

ds = whestbench.load_dataset("{{ repo_id }}", revision="{{ revision }}")
for mlp in whestbench.iter_mlps(ds):
    ...
```

