- **Created:** `{{ metadata.created_at_utc }}`

To re-bake locally:

```bash
whest dataset bake \
    --seed {{ metadata.seed }} \
    --n-mlps {{ metadata.n_mlps }} \
    --n-samples {{ metadata.n_samples }} \
    --width {{ metadata.width }} \
    --depth {{ metadata.depth }} \
    --split {{ split }} \
    --output ./my-bake{% if metadata.backend == "torch" %} \
    --torch{% endif %}
```

Bit-exact reproducibility requires the same `whestbench` and `faker` versions; statistical reproducibility (means within ~3e-5) holds across hardware on the `torch` backend.

